Profil Recherche=20

Le LISN (Laboratoire Interdisciplinaire des Sciences du Num=C3=A9rique) =
est une unit=C3=A9 mixte (UMR 9015), de l=E2=80=99Universit=C3=A9 =
Paris-Saclay et du CNRS. Ce laboratoire cr=C3=A9=C3=A9 au 1er Janvier =
2021 regroupe des enseignants/chercheurs et des chercheurs du LRI =
(Laboratoire de recherche et Informatique) et du LIMSI (Laboratoire =
d=E2=80=99Informatique pour la M=C3=A9canique et les Sciences de =
l=E2=80=99Ing=C3=A9nieur) dans cinq d=C3=A9partements de recherche dont =
le d=C3=A9partement Sciences des donn=C3=A9es auquel est rattach=C3=A9e =
l'=C3=A9quipe LaHDAK.
 =20
Les th=C3=A8mes de recherche l=E2=80=99enseignant(e)/chercheur(e)  =
recrut=C3=A9(e) s=E2=80=99inscriront en priorit=C3=A9 dans le domaine de =
la repr=C3=A9sentation des connaissances et du raisonnement. Ses =
activit=C3=A9s de recherche devront s=E2=80=99int=C3=A9grer au sein du =
d=C3=A9partement Sciences des donn=C3=A9es et plus sp=C3=A9cifiquement =
de l=E2=80=99=C3=A9quipe LaHDAK du LISN (issu du LRI) avec une =
pr=C3=A9f=C3=A9rence pour les axes de recherche suivants :=20
(1) fouille de donn=C3=A9es et d=C3=A9couverte de connaissances (cl=C3=A9s=
,  r=C3=A8gles,  motifs  de  graphe) =20
(2) qualit=C3=A9  des  donn=C3=A9es  et  des  connaissances (validit=C3=A9=
,  inconsistance  et  incertitude) =20
(3) raisonnement  dans  les  graphes  de connaissances et ontologies
(4) liage de donn=C3=A9es et gestion de l=E2=80=99identit=C3=A9 dans le =
Web.=20

Les comp=C3=A9tences souhait=C3=A9es sont prioritairement =
m=C3=A9thodologiques avec une ouverture par exemple sur les applications =
aux donn=C3=A9es agronomiques, m=C3=A9dicales, a=C3=A9ronautiques, des =
entreprises.  Une ouverture aux probl=C3=A8mes de la bioinformatique ou =
de l=E2=80=99IoT sera =C3=A9galement appr=C3=A9ci=C3=A9e pour une =
int=C3=A9gration dans le d=C3=A9partement Sciences des donn=C3=A9es du =
laboratoire.


Profil Enseignement=20

M=C3=A9thodes p=C3=A9dagogiques innovantes : l=E2=80=99enseignement =
constitue l=E2=80=99une des missions qui fonde l=E2=80=99Universit=C3=A9. =
La question de la qualit=C3=A9 de la formation dispens=C3=A9e et de la =
qualit=C3=A9 des apprentissages des =C3=A9tudiants sont plus que jamais =
au c=C5=93ur des pr=C3=A9occupations de l=E2=80=99Universit=C3=A9 =
Paris-Saclay.
A ce titre, le profil enseignement (de ce poste) inclut une capacit=C3=A9 =
=C3=A0 :
- interroger ses pratiques p=C3=A9dagogiques,
- exp=C3=A9rimenter des modalit=C3=A9s p=C3=A9dagogiques innovantes,
- concevoir les s=C3=A9quences d=E2=80=99enseignement selon des =
objectifs d=E2=80=99apprentissage et des comp=C3=A9tences explicites
- partager ses m=C3=A9thodes/exp=C3=A9riences et contribuer ainsi =C3=A0 =
enrichir la r=C3=A9flexion sur la p=C3=A9dagogie au sein de r=C3=A9seaux =
et structures d'=C3=A9changes

Fili=C3=A8res de formation concern=C3=A9es : les deux ann=C3=A9es de DUT =
informatique, le DUT informatique par apprentissage, le DUT informatique =
en un an, les licences professionnelles en informatique : S=C3=A9curit=C3=A9=
 des R=C3=A9seaux et des Syst=C3=A8mes Informatiques (SRSI) et =
Programmation Internet et Syst=C3=A8mes Mobiles (PRISM).

L=E2=80=99enseignant(e) recrut=C3=A9(e) devra enseigner l=E2=80=99informat=
ique dans les fili=C3=A8res mentionn=C3=A9es ci-dessus et notamment les =
mati=C3=A8res suivantes : Conception orient=C3=A9e objet (UML), bases de =
donn=C3=A9es, g=C3=A9nie logiciel. Des candidatures dont le profil =
permet, en plus, d=E2=80=99enseigner une des disciplines suivantes (sans =
ordre de priorit=C3=A9) seraient =C3=A9galement appr=C3=A9ci=C3=A9es : =
algorithmique et la programmation (C, C++, Java, ...), programmation des =
applications mobiles, programmation Web, syst=C3=A8mes d=E2=80=99exploitat=
ion, architecture des ordinateurs.

L=E2=80=99enseignant(e) recrut=C3=A9(e) devra s=E2=80=99investir dans =
les diff=C3=A9rentes responsabilit=C3=A9s p=C3=A9dagogiques, =
administratives et de communication du d=C3=A9partement (responsabilit=C3=A9=
 de fili=C3=A8re, etc.). Il/elle pourra =C3=AAtre sollicit=C3=A9(e) dans =
le cadre des actions de formation permanente.


************* For English =
**************************************************
Dear All,

An associate professor position in Computer Science is open at LISN - =
Laboratoire Interdisciplinaire des Sciences du Num=C3=A9rique (merging =
to lab's teams : LIMSI www.limsi.fr and  LRI www.lri.fr) at the =
University Paris Saclay.=20

The recruited person will be assigned to IUT d'Orsay for teaching  and =
to the Data Science department of LISN for her research activity in the =
LaHDAK team - Large-scale Heterogeneous DAta and Knowledge =
(https://lahdak.lri.fr/).=20

Contacts

* Research :=20
- Nicole Bidoit (nicole.bidoit@lri.fr): head of LaHDAK team
- Fatiha Sa=C3=AFs (fatiha.sais@lri.fr) : co-head of LaHDAK team

* Teaching :=20
- Francesca Fiorenzi (francesca.fiorenzi@universite-paris-saclay.fr) : =
head of the computer science department of IUT d'Orsay and=20
- Banafsheh Farang-Hariri =
(banafsheh.farang-hariri@universite-paris-saclay.fr) : co-head the =
computer science department of IUT d'Orsay

---------------------------------------
Detailed information for this the position: =20

Research=20

The LISN (Interdisciplinary Laboratory of Digital Sciences) is a mixed =
unit (UMR 9015), of the University of Paris-Saclay and the CNRS. This =
laboratory, created on January 1, 2021, brings together teachers / =
researchers and researchers from LRI (Computer Science Research =
Laboratory) and LIMSI (Computer Science Laboratory for Mechanics and =
Engineering Sciences) in five research departments including the =
Department of Data Sciences.

The research activities of the recruited lecturer/researcher should fall =
in the field of knowledge representation and reasoning. Her research =
activities should be coherent with the Data Sciences department and more =
particularly with the LaHDAK team at LISN (from LRI). The following =
lines of research are a priority:
(1)	data mining and knowledge discovery (keys, rules, graph =
patterns)
(2)	data and knowledge quality (validity, inconsistency and =
uncertainty)
(3)	reasoning in knowledge graphs and ontologies
(4)	data linking and identity management in the Web.=20

The expected skills of the recruited teacher/researcher are primarily =
methodological with an opening, for example, on applications to =
agronomic, medical, aeronautical and business data. An interest to =
bioinformatics or IoT issues will also be appreciated for integration =
into the data science department of the laboratory.


Teaching

Develop university's educative works including those related to =
entrance, examinations, and teaching animation: Teaching is one of the =
missions of the University. The quality of teaching and the quality of =
student learning are more than ever at the heart of Paris-Saclay =
University.

As such, the teaching profile includes an ability to:
-  question his teaching practices,
-  experiment with innovative teaching methods,
-  design teaching sequences according to learning objectives and =
explicit skills
-  share his methods / experiences and thus contribute to enrich the =
reflection on pedagogy within networks and exchange structures.

Training courses concerned: the two-year DUT in computer science, the =
DUT in computer science by apprenticeship, the one-year DUT in computer =
science, professional computer science bachelor=E2=80=99s degree (L3): =
Security of Computer Networks and Systems (SRSI) and Internet and Mobile =
Systems Programming (PRISM).

The lecturer recruited will be required to teach computer science in the =
abovementioned subjects and in particular the following subjects: =
object-oriented design (UML), databases, software engineering. =
Applications whose profile also allows them to teach one of the =
following subjects (in no order of priority) would also be appreciated: =
algorithms and programming (C, C++, Java, ...), programming of mobile =
applications, web programming, operating systems, computer architecture.

The recruited lecturer will have to be involved in the various =
pedagogical, administrative and communication responsibilities of the =
department (course responsibility, etc.). He/she may be called upon to =
take part in continuing education activities.



